<h5 style="text-align: left; font-size: 12pt; margin-top: 6.00pt; margin-bottom: 2.00pt;"><b><font
	 style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 18pt; font-weight: bold;" face="Arial"
	 size="5">Resize and Reposition Things in a Roster</font></b></h5>
<p style="text-align: left; margin-top: 0.00pt; margin-bottom: 0.00pt;">&#160;</p>
<p style="text-align: left; margin-top: 0.00pt; margin-bottom: 0.00pt;"><b><font
	 style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 10pt; font-weight: bold;" face="Arial"
	 size="2">â€¢&#160;Change roster size</font></b></p>
<p style="text-align: left; margin-left: 10.80pt; margin-top: 0.00pt; margin-bottom: 0.00pt;"><font
	 style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 10pt;" face="Arial" size="2">Select
 the roster by clicking on the gray space in any cell. You will see eight
 small black squares [the resize handles] around the edges at the corners
 and sides of the roster. Move the mouse pointer on top of any resize handle
 until the mouse pointer changes to a double-headed arrow. Click and drag
 to the desired size. CSPro will automatically create or remove scrollbars
 as needed.</font></p>
<p style="text-align: left; margin-top: 0.00pt; margin-bottom: 0.00pt;">&#160;</p>
<p style="text-align: left; margin-top: 0.00pt; margin-bottom: 0.00pt;"><b><font
	 style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 10pt; font-weight: bold;" face="Arial"
	 size="2">â€¢&#160;Change column width</font></b></p>
<p style="text-align: left; margin-left: 10.80pt; margin-top: 0.00pt; margin-bottom: 0.00pt;"><font
	 style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 10pt;" face="Arial" size="2">Move
 the mouse pointer over the right edge of the column you wish to resize
 until the mouse cursor changes to a double-headed arrow. Click and drag
 to the desired width.</font></p>
<p style="text-align: left; margin-top: 0.00pt; margin-bottom: 0.00pt;">&#160;</p>
<p style="text-align: left; margin-top: 0.00pt; margin-bottom: 0.00pt;"><b><font
	 style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 10pt; font-weight: bold;" face="Arial"
	 size="2">â€¢&#160;Change row height</font></b></p>
<p style="text-align: left; margin-left: 10.80pt; margin-top: 0.00pt; margin-bottom: 0.00pt;"><font
	 style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 10pt;" face="Arial" size="2">Move
 the mouse pointer over the bottom edge of the row you wish to resize until
 the mouse cursor changes to a double-headed arrow. Click and drag to the
 desired height.</font></p>
<p style="text-align: left; margin-left: 10.80pt; margin-top: 0.00pt; margin-bottom: 0.00pt;">&#160;</p>
<p style="text-align: left; margin-top: 0.00pt; margin-bottom: 0.00pt;"><b><font
	 style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 10pt; font-weight: bold;" face="Arial"
	 size="2">â€¢&#160;Change order of columns</font></b></p>
<p style="text-align: left; margin-left: 10.80pt; margin-top: 0.00pt; margin-bottom: 0.00pt;"><font
	 style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 10pt;" face="Arial" size="2">At
 data entry time, fields are keyed in the same order in which they appear
 in the roster columns, left to right (or top to bottom if the roster orientation
 is vertical). To change the order of columns, click on the column heading
 and drag to the desired position. A gray separator line will tell you
 where you are about to drop the selected column.</font></p>
<p style="text-align: left; margin-top: 0.00pt; margin-bottom: 0.00pt;">&#160;</p>
